OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMicroplastics found in     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffresh Antarctic snow       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Scientists have for the first time     
OL,6, found microplastics in freshly fallen  
OL,7, Antarctic snow.                        
OL,9,FResearchers from the University of     
OL,10,FCanterbury in New Zealand collected    
OL,11,Fsamples from 19 sites in Antarctica and
OL,12,Feach contained tiny plastic fragments. 
OL,14,FMicroplastics stem from the erosion of 
OL,15,Fplastic materials and are smaller than 
OL,16,Fa grain of rice - sometimes even       
OL,17,Finvisible to the naked eye.            
OL,19,FThe researchers found an average of 29 
OL,20,Fparticles per litre of melted snow.    
